GONG ARK LEE, Appellant, v. John D. NAGLE as Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of San Francisco, Cal., Appellee. No. 6396. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 18, 1931.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

. Pursuant to motion of counsel for appellant, and agreed to by counsel for appellee, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and' that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
